The two presidents slammed into the [[Chilean Navy|Chilean Navy's]] ''[[Esmeralda (BE-43)|Esmeralda]]'' training ship, where they crossed a section of the [[Panama Canal]]. Chile is the third largest and the first Latin American country to use the Canal.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.radioagricultura.cl/internacional/2018/07/10/presidente-pinera-firma-acuerdos-de-cooperacion-en-panama.html|title=Presidente Piñera firma acuerdos de cooperación en Panamá|last=Agricultura|first=Radio|work=Radio Agricultura|access-date=2018-07-11|language=es-LA}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.panamaon.com/noticias/politica/48758-sebastian-pinera-el-canal-ampliado-es-una-obra-maestra-de-la-ingenieria.html|title=Sebastián Piñera: El Canal ampliado es una obra maestra de la ingeniería|last=www.panamaon.com|date=2018-07-11|work=PanamaOn|access-date=2018-07-11|language=es-ES}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.efe.com/efe/america/politica/pinera-recorre-el-canal-de-panama-a-bordo-del-esmeralda-y-destaca-la-ampliacion/20000035-3680409|title=Piñera recorre el Canal de Panamá a bordo del Esmeralda y destaca la ampliación|work=www.efe.com|access-date=2018-07-11|language=es}}</ref> |- |{{USA}} |[[Idaho]] |10–11 July |{{further|Chile–United States relations}}As an end to the third international tour, Piñera went to Sun Valley 2018 technology forum, where he met with leaders of major digital companies: [[Tim Cook]] ([[Apple Inc.|Apple]]), [[Sundar Pichai]] ([[Google]]), [[Mark Zuckerberg]] ([[Facebook]]), [[Ana Botín]] ([[Banco Santander|Santander Group]]), [[Marcos Galperin|Marcos Galperín]] ([[MercadoLibre]]), [[Reed Hastings]] ([[Netflix]]) and [[Jeff Bezos]] ([[Amazon (company)|Amazon]]), the latter with talks about Amazon starting in Chile. Sebastian Pinera stressed that these meetings analyzed strategic alliances with Chile in terms of education, state modernization and digital economy.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnnchile.com/tendencias/por-que-el-presidente-pinera-se-reunio-con-mark-zuckerberg_20180711/|title=¿Por qué el Presidente Piñera se reunió con Mark Zuckerberg? - CNN Chile|last=Chile|first=CNN|work=CNN Chile|access-date=2018-07-12|language=es-LA}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.publimetro.cl/cl/noticias/2018/07/11/presidente-pinera-sostiene-reuniones-con-mark-zuckerberg-y-jeff-bezzos.html|title=Presidente Piñera sostiene reuniones con líderes de Amazon y Facebook en Estados Unidos|work=Publimetro Chile|access-date=2018-07-12|language=es-ES}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.larepublica.co/globoeconomia/pinera-concreta-reunion-con-jeff-bezos-en-medio-del-interes-de-que-amazon-se-instale-en-chile-2748476|title=Piñera concreta reunión con Bezos en medio del interés de que Amazon llegue a Chile|last=S.A.S.|first=Editorial La República|access-date=2018-07-12|language=es-CO}}</ref> |- |{{MEX}} |[[Puerto Vallarta]] |23–24 July |{{further|Chile–Mexico relations}} At the XIII [[Pacific Alliance]] Summit, Piñera celebrated the "new phase" of the group, also commemorating the [[Mercosur]] approach and mentioned that it intends to strengthen ties with the 55 alliance observer countries. The countries of the Pacific Alliance and Mercusul envisage an agenda for 2030 with UN objectives. Piñera held bilateral meetings with [[Michel Temer]] ([[Brazil]]), [[Enrique Peña Nieto]] ([[Mexico]]) and [[Tabaré Vásquez]] ([[Uruguay]]).<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.elnuevodiario.com.ni/internacionales/470417-inicio-alianza-pacifico/|title=Piñera celebra el inicio de una "nueva etapa" en la Alianza del Pacífico - El Nuevo Diario|access-date=2018-07-28|language=es-LA}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.eleconomista.com.mx/empresas/Alianza-del-Pacifico-con-nuevos-brios-de-libre-comercio-20180724-0094.html|title=Alianza del Pacífico, con nuevos bríos de libre comercio - El Economista|access-date=2018-07-28|language=es-LA}}</ref> |- |- |{{COL}} |[[Bogotá|Bogota]] |7 August |{{further|Chile–Colombia relations}}He attended the Ceremony of Possession of the President of Colombia [[Iván Duque Márquez|Iván Duque]]. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.eldiario.es/politica/Pinera-Bogota-Chile-excelentes-Duque_0_801070515.html|title=Piñera dice en Bogotá que Chile mantendrá excelentes relaciones con Duque|work=eldiario.es|access-date=2018-08-08|language=es}}</ref> |- |{{USA}} |[[New York City|New York]] [[Washington, D.C.]] |25–28 September |{{further|Chile–United States relations}}In his speech at the 73rd [[United Nations General Assembly|UN General Assembly]], Piñera said that Chile "will help Venezuelans with all the instruments of international law to recover their liberties, democracy and respect for human rights."
On September 28, he met [[Donald Trump]] at the [[White House]]. The American President said that [[Venezuela]] is a "disaster" and needs to be "clean". Piñera agreed on the situation in [[Venezuela]], but said he opposed a military intervention in the country. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.infobae.com/america/america-latina/2018/09/27/sebastian-pinera-en-la-onu-chile-utilizara-todos-los-mecanismos-para-colaborar-con-la-recuperacion-de-la-libertad-en-venezuela/|title=Sebastián Piñera, en la ONU: "Chile utilizará todos los mecanismos para colaborar con la recuperación de la libertad en Venezuela"|work=Infobae|access-date=2018-10-07|language=es-LA}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://g1.globo.com/mundo/noticia/2018/09/28/trump-diz-que-venezuela-e-um-desastre-que-precisa-de-limpeza.ghtml|title=Trump diz que Venezuela é um 'desastre' que precisa de 'limpeza'|work=G1|access-date=2018-10-07|language=pt-BR}}</ref> |}
